---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SchemaMarkup from "../../components/SchemaMarkup.astro";
import Icon from "../../components/Icon.astro";

// Make this page dynamic via SSR
export const prerender = false;

const publishDate = new Date("December 7 2026");
const author = "The Valley Clean Team";
const readTime = "5 min read";

const isPublished = new Date().getTime() >= publishDate.getTime();

---

<BaseLayout
  title="Last-Minute Touches Before In-Laws Arrive"
  description={isPublished ? "Full Article: Last-Minute Touches Before Your In-Laws Arrive" : "Coming Soon: Last-Minute Touches Before Your In-Laws Arrive"}
  noindex={!isPublished}
  ogImage="https://storage.googleapis.com/msgsndr/iKQIBhpKVL2XVPgU7HMd/media/6920802945dc047d65b4ec5d.png"
>
  <SchemaMarkup
    type="article"
    title="Last-Minute Touches Before Your In-Laws Arrive"
    description="In-laws arriving soon? Follow our quick checklist for last-minute cleaning touches that make a massive impact and guarantee a great first impression."
    publishDate="December 7 2026"
    author={author}
  />
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#FFA985]/20 text-[#FFA985] rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-6">
          Humor/Pain Point
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Last-Minute Touches Before Your In-Laws Arrive
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          {isPublished ? "Expert Cleaning Guide" : "Coming December 7 2026."}
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4 text-gray-400 mb-8">
          <span>December 7 2026</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>{readTime}</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>By {author}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Toggle based on Published Date -->
  {isPublished ? (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <!-- TODO: REPLACE THIS SECTION WITH YOUR ACTUAL BLOG CONTENT -->
          <h2>How Can I Quickly Prepare My Home for an In-Laws Visit?</h2>
<p><strong>Preparing your home for in-laws in The Shoals & Surrounding Areas can be a breeze with a few strategic last-minute touches. Focus on high-impact areas like the bathroom, kitchen, and guest room. Remember, it's about making a great impression with minimal effort.</strong></p>
<p>When your in-laws decide to drop in, it can feel like a race against the clock. But don't stress! With our straightforward tips, you can transform panic into preparation.</p>

<h3>Focus on the Essentials</h3>
<p>First things first—prioritize the areas where your in-laws will spend the most time. Concentrate on these key spaces:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>The Bathroom:</strong> Ensure it's spotless. A gleaming sink and fresh towels go a long way.</li>
  <li><strong>The Kitchen:</strong> Clear countertops and a clean floor make the space inviting.</li>
  <li><strong>The Guest Room:</strong> Fresh linens and a tidy nightstand create a welcoming atmosphere.</li>
</ul>
<p>These are high-traffic zones where a little effort yields maximum results.</p>

<h3>Quick Decluttering Tips</h3>
<p>A cluttered space can feel chaotic. Here's how to quickly declutter:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Use Baskets:</strong> Gather loose items into decorative baskets to keep things organized.</li>
  <li><strong>Hide the Unnecessary:</strong> Stow away non-essential items in closets or under beds.</li>
  <li><strong>Surface Sweep:</strong> Clear tables and countertops for a cleaner look.</li>
</ul>
<p>These simple steps can transform a room from messy to manageable in minutes.</p>

<h3>Make It Smell Inviting</h3>
<p>Smell is a powerful sense when it comes to first impressions. Here's how to make your home smell inviting:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Light Scented Candles:</strong> Choose calming scents like lavender or vanilla.</li>
  <li><strong>Use Air Fresheners:</strong> Opt for subtle, natural fragrances.</li>
  <li><strong>Simmer Potpourri:</strong> A pot of water with cinnamon sticks and citrus slices works wonders.</li>
</ul>
<p>These aromatic touches can create a warm and welcoming environment instantly.</p>

<h3>Final Touches: The Wow Factor</h3>
<p>Now that the essentials are in place, add a few final touches for that "wow" factor:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Fresh Flowers:</strong> A vase of fresh flowers in the living room adds elegance.</li>
  <li><strong>Personal Touches:</strong> Display family photos or personal mementos to create a homely vibe.</li>
  <li><strong>Soft Lighting:</strong> Use lamps instead of overhead lights for a cozy atmosphere.</li>
</ul>
<p>These details will show your in-laws that you care about creating a comfortable and stylish environment.</p>

<h3>Call to Action: Reclaim Your Time</h3>
<p><strong>With The Valley Clean Team, you can reclaim your time and ensure your home is always guest-ready. Our veteran-owned cleaning specialists serve The Shoals & Surrounding Areas with military precision and guaranteed results. Book your premium cleaning service today, and impress your in-laws without lifting a finger. Get your free quote now!</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  ) : (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white border-t border-gray-100 shadow-inner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-center">
          <Icon name="clock" class="w-16 h-16 text-[#FFA985] mx-auto mb-6" />
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-0">Article Coming Soon!</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 m-0">This article is locked and scheduled to automatically publish on <br/><strong class="text-gray-800 text-xl">December 7 2026</strong>.<br/>Check back then!</p>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition shadow-md no-underline">
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  )}
</BaseLayout>
